### Public Beta Releases

Throughout development, public beta releases were made available to the MiSTer FPGA community.

Major areas of development included:

- IGS023 video implementation
- ICS2115 sound implementation
- IGS025 and IGS027 protection support
- LPC2132 support for specific game variants
- Expanded game compatibility

### June 2026 Public Beta Release

The final known public beta release introduced:

- Single SDRAM support
- Updated MRA structure
- Continued game compatibility improvements
- Additional refinements and bug fixes

This release serves as the preservation baseline for this repository.

This repository was created to preserve the latest publicly available beta version of the PGM MiSTer FPGA Core and provide a centralized location for community testing, documentation, compatibility reports, and technical feedback.

Community Preservation Repository:
Created to preserve publicly available beta releases, technical documentation, and community findings for future reference.

### End of Public Beta Availability

In June 2026, the original repository was made private by Eizo Chiu, concluding the public beta period.

The original author's decision is respected.

This repository preserves the final publicly available beta version and associated documentation for historical and technical reference purposes.
